text: Sarah Mutch (born December 21, 1984) also known by nickname Skippy, is a Canadian fashion model and actress. She is best known for the Guess campaigns, Italian Vogue, Maxim covers and commercials. Mutch has also starred in movies including Chillerama, Funkytown and The Seamstress. ==Early life== Sarah was born in Vancouver, British Columbia. Since her childhood, she has been interested in modeling and acting. ==Career== Sarah began her professional career when she was discovered by Jeff Palffy in Vancouver Canada. She moved to New York City to continue her career after a year into it. She made her acting debut in the TV series Smallville (2001-2011). Her magnum opus is the TV series Supernatural released in 2006. Sarah also played a major role in Jake 2.0. Sarah has appeared in the multiple shows and has made various appearances in magazines like Vogue, Cosmopolitan, and Elle. She took the lead role in the 2011 Canadian movie, Funkytown which debuted at the Toronto film festival in September 2010. She was featured on the May and June 2010 cover of Ocean Drive. ==Credits== ===Movies=== {| class="wikitable" |+ !Year !Movies !Role !Notes |- |2011 |Chillerama |Actor | |- |2011 |Funkytown |Actor | |- |2009 |The Seamstress |Actor | |} ===Television=== {| class="wikitable" |+ !Year !Television !Role !Notes |- |2009 |Stargate Universe |Actor | |- |2009 |Maxim Hot 100 |Actor | |- |2006 |Supernatural |Actor | |- |2005 |Smallville |Actor | |- |2005 |Jake 2.0 |Actor | |} ==Personal life== Sarah married real estate businessman Kurt Rappaport. Kurt is the CEO of the Beverly-Hills based Westside Estate Agency. They became engaged in 2015 and married in 2017.
